{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["occ"],"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@interface"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNMapSnapshotter"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"NSObject","preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)NSObject"}]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can change the snapshotter’s options at any time and reuse the snapshotter"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for multiple distinct snapshots; however, the snapshotter can only generate one"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"snapshot at a time. If you need to generate multiple snapshots concurrently,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"create multiple snapshotter objects."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For an interactive map, use the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView","isActive":true},{"text":" class. Both ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapSnapshotter","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView","isActive":true},{"text":" are compatible with offline packs managed by the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOfflineStorage","isActive":true},{"text":" class.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"From a snapshot, you can obtain an image and convert geographic coordinates to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the image’s coordinate space in order to superimpose markers and overlays. If"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you do not need offline map functionality, you can use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Snapshot"},{"type":"text","text":" class in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/mapbox\/MapboxStatic.swift\/"},{"type":"text","text":" to generate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"static map images with overlays."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Example","anchor":"Example","type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let camera = MLNMapCamera(lookingAtCenter: CLLocationCoordinate2D(latitude: 37.7184, longitude:","-122.4365), altitude: 100, pitch: 20, heading: 0)","","let options = MLNMapSnapshotOptions(styleURL: MLNStyle.satelliteStreetsStyleURL, camera: camera,","size: CGSize(width: 320, height: 480)) options.zoomLevel = 10","","let snapshotter = MLNMapSnapshotter(options: options)","snapshotter.start { (snapshot, error) in","    if let error = error {","        fatalError(error.localizedDescription)","    }","","    image = snapshot?.image","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":4,"text":"Related examples","anchor":"Related-examples","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"TODO: Create a static map snapshot, learn how to use the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapSnapshotter","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" to generate a static image based on an ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapSnapshotter","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"object’s style, camera, and view bounds.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNMapSnapshotter"}],"role":"symbol","title":"MLNMapSnapshotter","fragments":[{"text":"MLNMapSnapshotter","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNMapSnapshotter","roleHeading"